Usage: wyd <command> [flags]

a program to ask you what you're doing

Flags:
  -h, --help                    Show context-sensitive help.
  -v, --verbose                 enable verbose logging
  -d, --database-path=STRING    where to store the database

Commands:
  clients (client,c) add (a) --name=STRING
    add a client

  clients (client,c) list
    list all clients

  clients (client,c) delete (d) --name=STRING --id=INT-64
    delete a client

  projects (project,p) add (a) [flags]
    add a project

  projects (project,p) list [flags]
    list all projects

  projects (project,p) delete (d) --name=STRING --id=INT-64
    delete a project

  tasks (task,t) add --name=STRING --project=STRING
    add a task

  tasks (task,t) list [flags]
    list all tasks

  tasks (task,t) delete --name=STRING --id=INT-64
    delete a task

Run "wyd <command> --help" for more information on a command.

